{"lemma":"كُلٌّ","slug":"كُلٌّ","root":"ك.ل.ل","root_slug":"ك-ل-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-ل-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"كُلّ","root":"كلل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":359},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n43086"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D9%8F%D9%84%D9%8C%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"each one, everyone"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"each, every (with following indefinite noun in the genitive)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"whole, all (with following definite noun in the genitive)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Akkadian 𒆕𒀀𒁉 (kalûm), Ge'ez ኵል (kʷəll), Ugaritic 𐎋𐎍 (kl), Phoenician 𐤊𐤋 (kl), Classical Syriac ܟܾܠ (kul). From Proto-Semitic *kʷall- or Proto-Semitic *kull-, ultimately from Proto-Afroasiatic *ʔa-kʷall-."},"ipa":["/kull/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n43086","headword_ar":"كُلٌّ","root":"kl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"when preceded by a negative and followed by an exception, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any one;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the Kur, xxxviii. 13,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ino kul~N A_il~aA ka*~aba Alr~usula","text_ar":"اـِنْ كُلٌّ اـِلَّا كَذَّبَ الرُّسُلَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There was not any one but accused the apostles of lying."},{"kind":"text","text":"See also another ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lam~aA","text_ar":"لَمَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEoD","text_ar":"بَعْض"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa AlEaAlimu kul~u AlEaAlimi","text_ar":"هُوَ العَالِمُ كُلُّ العَالِمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is the possessor of knowledge, the entirety of the possessor of knowledge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means that he is one who has attained to the utmost degree of the quality thus attributed to him. (Sb, K, TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~amaA","text_ar":"كُلَّمَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whatever."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~amaA","text_ar":"كُلَّمَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whenever; as often as; every time that; in proportion as."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~amano","text_ar":"كُلَّمَنْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whoever."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}